The paper deals with the design of a centralized algorithm for the placement of Gateway UAVs in Flying Networks, with the aim of optimizing the backhaul network design. This involves taking into account the offered traffic and the future topologies of the network. The paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category, as it deals with the design of a network architecture for UAVs. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, as it deals with the optimization of network capacity. Additionally, the paper may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category, as it may involve securing the communication between the UAVs and the ground users. The paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category, as it deals with the control of the UAVs in order to optimize the network performance. Finally, the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, as it may involve the use of machine learning algorithms to optimize the network performance.
